Under Instruction from Cobbora Holding Company Pty Ltd (CHC), CBRE Agribusiness and Milling Stuart Pty Ltd are pleased to present for sale Glenroy, a mixed agricultural landholding in the Central West region of New South Wales.

Glenroy comprises an approximate area of 2,438 hectares rivalling the largest landholdings in the region. Comprising quality soils and level to undulating topography underpinned by favourable climate characteristics, Glenroy is well suited to a range of breeding/fattening and winter crop production enterprises.

Key Investment Highlights 


Scale 

Comprising 2,438* contiguous hectares of productive land well suited to a range of cropping and grazing enterprises. 
Topography & Soils 
Rising from gently undulating red and red brown earth soils to small areas of timbered ridges and low hilltops with an average elevation of 460* metres above sea level.


Diversity 

A diverse enterprise mix comprising 800* hectares of cultivation, 1,339* hectares of arable grazing land, the remaining land consists of timbered ridges, shelter and support area.


Location 

Located centrally to Dubbo, Wellington, Dunedoo and Mudgee in the Mid-Western region of New South Wales, Glenroy benefits from convenient access to a range of markets, services and amenities resulting in excellent comparative advantage in reduced freight/transport costs.


Water 

Comprising 40 strategically placed dams with large catchments and storage capacities provide the ability to be able to utilise the total grazing area of the property.


Glenroy presents a rare opportunity to purchase a property with significant scale and production capability. The offering of a large scale landholding in the Dunedoo - Gulgong region is unprecedented in recent years with sales in the surrounding area rivalling the size of Glenroy scarce and seldom offered to the public market. 

Glenroy is being offered for sale via Auction, Thursday 15 December 2016 at 11 am Australian Eastern Daylight Time (AEDT) at the Dunedoo Golf Club, Wargundy Street, Dunedoo NSW 2844.

Under Instruction from Cobbora Holding Company Pty Ltd (CHC), CBRE Agribusiness and Milling Stuart Pty Ltd are pleased to present for sale Avondale, a mixed agricultural landholding in the Central West region of New South Wales.

Avondale comprises an approximate area of 3,246 hectares rivalling the largest landholdings in the region. Comprising quality soils and level to undulating topography underpinned by favourable climate characteristics, Avondale is well suited to a range of breeding/fattening and winter crop production enterprises.

Key Investment Highlights 

Scale 

Comprising 3,245* hectares of productive land well suited to a range of cropping and grazing enterprises. 


Topography & Soils 

Rising from fertile alluvial creek flats along the Sandy Creek through gently undulating red basalt and red brown earth arable grazing land to small areas of timbered ridges and low hilltops with an average elevation of 440* metres above sea level.


Diversity 

Diverse enterprise mix comprising 1,600* hectares of cultivation, 1,341* hectares quality arable grazing land with the remaining area consisting of timbered ridges, shelter and support area.


Location 

Located centrally to Dubbo, Wellington, Dunedoo and Mudgee in the Central West region of New South Wales, Avondale benefits from convenient access to a range of markets, services and amenities resulting in excellent comparative advantage in reduced freight/transport costs.


Water 

Comprising 73 dams utilising contour banks to enhance the catchment efficiency backed by seven* kilometres of largely double frontage to the Sandy Creek and numerous bores supplying a network of reticulated water systems ensures full utilisation of the grazing area.

Avondale presents a rare opportunity to purchase a property with significant scale and production capability. The offering of a large scale landholding in the Dunedoo - Gulgong region is unprecedented in recent years with sales in the surrounding area rivalling the size of Avondale scarce and seldom offered to the public market. 

Avondale is being offered for sale via Auction on Thursday 15 December 2016 at 11 am Australian Eastern Daylight Time (AEDT) at the Dunedoo Golf Club, Wargundy Street, Dunedoo NSW 2844.

Under Instruction from Cobbora Holding Company Pty Ltd (CHC), CBRE Agribusiness and Milling Stuart Pty Ltd are pleased to present for sale Tallawang, an arable landholding in the Central West region of New South Wales.

Tallawang comprises an approximate area of 347 hectares of quality soils and level to slightly undulating topography underpinned by favourable climate characteristics, Tallawang is well suited to grain and fodder production enterprises.    


Key Investment Highlights 

Scale 

Comprising 347* hectares of productive arable land well suited to a range of cropping and fodder production enterprises with the added ability to incorporate a high-performance grazing enterprise. 


Topography & Soils 

Gently undulating topography with an even balance of red and red brown earths transitioning to low sandy loam ridges with an average elevation of 500* metres above sea level and a southerly aspect.


Production

Comprising 327* hectares of cultivation currently under winter crop with the remaining land utilised as grazing and support area. 


Location 

Located centrally to Dubbo, Wellington, Dunedoo and Mudgee in the Central West region of New South Wales providing convenient access to a range of markets, services and amenities.


Access 

Direct frontage to the Castlereagh Highway provides ease of access both north and south as well as east and west via the Golden Highway and associated benefits from excellent comparative advantage with regard to freight and transport costs. 


Accommodation 

Two quality houses set in spacious lawn gardens provide a number of comfortable accommodation options for owners or employees/rental opportunities. 


Tallawang presents a rare opportunity to purchase production capability in the Dunedoo- Gulgong region. Land in the surrounding area rivalling the quality of Tallawang is scarce and seldom offered to the public market. 

Tallawang is being offered for sale via Auction, Thursday 15 December 2016 at 11am Australian Eastern Daylight Time (AEDT) at the Dunedoo Golf Club, Wargundy Street, Dunedoo NSW 2844.
